      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T11:18:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "question: is it because of code deduplication that you use the lustre enrichment function?\n\nMore generally, is the lustre extension required to be installed to use the ldiskfs one? If that\u0027s the case, why the ldiskfs is not directly an extension of lustre? I donnot recall if this is possible or not..",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 244,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 244,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "fd819ca48297ad804659e4ba0ab1e7b1b7365587",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "150272c0_2de59e61",
        "filename": "librobinhood/src/plugins/ldiskfs/filter.c",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 244,
      "author": {
        "id": 1039247
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T14:28:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is primarily for code deduplication, but also for simplicity. For example the filters we may want to use in the ldiskfs backend are already all defined in the lustre enricher.\n\nAs it is currently implemented, the ldiskfs backend requires the lustre enricher to be used. In the current state of the project, it won\u0027t even be built if the lustre enricher is disabled at setup time.\nThe ldiskfs plugin cannot be integrated in the posix plugin, as it only reads data from the block devices themselves, and does require neither the filesystems to be mounted nor a lustre server to be running.",
      "parentUuid": "e5e243b3_90e594ae",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 244,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 244,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "fd819ca48297ad804659e4ba0ab1e7b1b7365587",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9c8ad6ef_22a29816",
        "filename": "librobinhood/src/plugins/ldiskfs/filter.c",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 244,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017196
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T09:48:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Okay, I searched in the repository and I now clearly see what ldiskfs is, as it is not an extension of a given plugin, that\u0027s an independent one.\n\nBut for the build of the ldiskfs plugin, you do not have to require that the lustre enriche is built, only that lustre is available. So I think that the enricher code needs to be taken out from the lustre extension if you want to avoid code duplication. But I will not block this patch for this reason.",
      "parentUuid": "150272c0_2de59e61",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 244,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 244,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "fd819ca48297ad804659e4ba0ab1e7b1b7365587",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
